// GAP (atomic-vs-nonatomic race, confirmed 2026-07-18): a global used with
// @atomic_* in a concurrent context is an "atomic cell" — plain access must
// also be atomic. The "is atomic cell?" determination is whole-program, but the
// "flag plain access" check only fires for accesses lexically inside a
// spawning/spawned function. Move the plain write into a helper → missed.
// EXPECTED: compile error. OBSERVED: clean compile (TSan-confirmed race).
// Control: the identical plain write placed directly in main() IS rejected.
u32 g_ctr;
void worker() { u32 v = @atomic_add(&g_ctr, 1); }
void poke() { g_ctr = 5; }        // plain write to an atomic cell via helper
u32 main() {
    spawn worker();
    poke();
    return 0;
}
